My fiance and I had never really had chestnuts before. I found that while they were an interesting contrast to the brussells sprouts, I would probably try with almonds next time. Overall very simple to make and I will make again with different nuts.

Rating: 3
I really liked this recipe. I used slivered almonds and added garlic. After the sprouts were steamed I sliced them all in half and placed them faced down in the pan to get them a little brown and crispy. Before making this recipe my husband said he did not like brussels sprouts but he didn't leave a single one on his plate.

